**\#\#\# DEV Movies**

A responsive React web application that allows users to search and explore detailed information about movies using the OMDb API.

**\#\#\# Prerequisites**

* \-Node.js (v18+)  
    
* \-npm or yarn

**\#\#\# Installation**

* \`\`\`bash  
    
* git clone [https://github.com/your-user/dev-movies.git](https://github.com/your-user/dev-movies.git)  
    
* cd dev-movies  
    
* npm install

**\#\#\# Architecture Overview**

The application is structured with separation of concerns and scalability in mind:

* Component-based structure: Each component is modular, with separate logic, styles, and responsibilities.  
    
* Context API: Centralized state management using MovieContext to handle global states like selected movie, search term, and pagination.  
    
* Tailwind CSS: Utility-first styling for a clean and responsive design.  
    
* Vitest \+ Testing Library: Lightweight unit and integration testing setup for components.  
    
  src/  
  ├── assets/               \# Static images (fallbacks, logo)  
  ├── components/      \# UI components (SearchBar, MovieModal, etc.)  
  ├── context/              \# MovieContext \+ custom hooks  
  ├── types/                 \# TypeScript interfaces  
  └── \_\_tests\_\_/          \# Component test suites

**\#\#\# Technical Decisions**

* TypeScript was used for type safety and better developer experience.  
    
* Context API instead of Redux, considering the app’s scale and simplicity.  
    
* Tailwind CSS was chosen for rapid and consistent UI development.  
    
* OMDb API used as a reliable public movie information source.  
    
* Testing with Vitest and Testing Library to ensure component correctness.
